	(text "Software Flashing Instructions:\nWhen the raw board is brand new, or if the code crashes the USB line, \nyou must use this manual sequence to push a new program:\n1. PRESS and HOLD the physical 'BOOT' button (SW202).\n2. PRESS and RELEASE the physical 'RESET' button (SW201) once.\n3. RELEASE the 'BOOT' button (SW202).\n4. In the Arduino IDE, click the 'Upload' arrow button. \n\n\nAfterwards, to never have to press the buttons again while testing code on the bench:\n\n1. Inside the Arduino IDE, open the 'Tools' dropdown menu.\n2. Look for the setting called 'USB CDC On Boot'.\n3. Change this setting from \"Disabled\" to \"ENABLED\".\n4. Upload your program using Method A one final time."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 217.424 61.214 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "60b2d494-3eb8-481d-84cd-15882105ebfa")
	)
